Title : Ahta Indian Reserve No. 3
Text : '''Ahta Indian Reserve No. 3''', officially '''Ahta 3''', is an [[Indian reserve]] on [[Bond Sound]] on the [[British Columbia Coast|Coast of British Columbia]], Canada, located at the mouth of the [[Ahta River]].<ref>[http://apps.gov.bc.ca/pub/bcgnws/names/65363.html BC Names/GeoBC entry "Ahta 3 (Indian reserve)"]</ref>  It is under the governance of the [[Kwikwasut'inuxw Haxwa'mis First Nation]] and is 7.1 hectares in area.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://pse5-esd5.ainc-inac.gc.ca/FNP/Main/Search/RVDetail.aspx?RESERVE_NUMBER=06980&lang=eng |title=Indian and Northern Affairs Canada "Reserve/Settlement/Village Detail" |access-date=2014-05-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140503083834/http://pse5-esd5.ainc-inac.gc.ca/FNP/Main/Search/RVDetail.aspx?RESERVE_NUMBER=06980&lang=eng |archive-date=2014-05-03 |dead-url=yes |df= }}</ref>

The reserve is on the site of a former village variously spelled "Hata", "Hada", or "Ahta".<ref>[http://apps.gov.bc.ca/pub/bcgnws/names/54850.html BC Names "Hata (Former First Nations village)"]</ref>

